1
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:43,831
Sorry, old-timer...

2
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,231
...but you're only part poison,
and I'm hungry for meat.

3
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:50,670
Getting a little thirsty too.

4
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,152
Taggart?

5
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:02,673
Bowen, go easy.

6
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:08,312
You peckerwoods just raised hell
with our supper.

7
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,356
Find any water?

8
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:05,234
I appreciate humor, boys...

9
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:08,756
...but I'm beginning to think
you're cutting it a mite thin.

10
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,672
What else we got to do?

11
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,391
What did you find?

12
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:20,269
Ten thousand gallons of sand,
that's what we found.

13
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:22,988
We had you shaking, didn't we, Cable?

14
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,272
Hold him, boy. Get over there.

15
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,956
It's just like you said, Hogue.

16
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:35,078
There's water enough for two,
but not for three.

17
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:38,437
You damn fool. You had us.

18
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,830
You just wouldn't pull the trigger.

19
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:45,676
- Because you're yellow.
- Yeah, he's yellow. Just plain yellow.

20
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:49,196
- Hell, you're yellow, Hogue.
- Cable is yellow.

21
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,635
<i>Old Cable's yellow</i>

22
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,837
<i>Old Cable is white</i>
<i>Old Cable's dying</i>

23
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,319
<i>But that's all right</i>

24
00:02:57,040 --> 00:03:02,831
<i>Taggart and Bowen as slick as you please</i>
<i>Took all the water and left for the trees</i>

25
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,231
Hey, fellas. Leave me a little.

26
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,073
- Please.
- It's all yours, Cable.

27
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:13,439
Fifty thousand gallons of sand.

28
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:20,078
- We've got your water, Cable.
- Yellow!

29
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,356
Call me yellow.

30
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:26,079
Leave me to dry and blow away.

31
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:29,075
Sing a song about it!

32
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:32,909
Laugh at old Cable Hogue, huh?

33
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:38,555
I'll get out! I'll get out!

34
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:41,280
Don't you worry none about that!

35
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,358
You just...

36
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:46,115
...worry about when I get out.

37
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:49,350
I'll find you, Taggart.

38
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,557
You, Bowen,
you mealy-mouthed little pimp.

39
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:57,555
You never could tell gold-shine from
lizard shit, and there's a big difference.

40
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,836
A big difference!

41
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:04,113
I'll live to spit on your graves!

42
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,835
<i>Old Cable's yellow</i>

43
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,828
Yellow!

44
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:22,793
We got your water.

45
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:41,432
Ain't had no water
since yesterday, Lord.

46
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,111
Getting a little thirsty.

47
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,390
Just thought I'd mention it. Amen.

48
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:52,117
Yesterday, I told you I was thirsty...

49
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:56,193
...and I thought you might
turn up some water.

50
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:02,151
Now, if I sinned,
you just send me a drop or two...

51
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,436
...and I won't do it no more...

52
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,955
...whatever in the hell it was I did.

53
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,711
I mean that, Lord.

54
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:26,030
Four days without water. You don't
think I've put in my suffering time...

55
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:29,793
...you ought to try going dry for a spell.

56
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:32,713
Listen to me. Listen to me.

57
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:37,670
If I don't get some soon,
I ain't gonna have no chance to repent.

58
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:44,476
Careful, now.
You're about to get my dander up.

59
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,433
Lord...

60
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,276
...you call it.

61
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,679
I'm just plain done in.

62
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,231
Amen.

63
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,671
Hogue...

64
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:55,037
...found it.

65
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:16,235
Told you I was gonna live.

66
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:21,071
This is Cable Hogue talking.
Hogue. Me.

67
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:24,835
Cable Hogue. Hogue. Me.

68
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,754
Me. I did it. Cable Hogue.

69
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,957
I found it. Me.

70
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,278
Wagons.

71
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,232
Stagecoaches.

72
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,834
Buckboards.

73
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,395
With kids and mamas.

74
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,273
People.

75
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:17,150
Going somewhere on a road.

76
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,151
And I'm on it.

77
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,514
Me and my water hole.

78
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,151
I whipped them bastards.

79
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:39,110
Now all I gotta do is wait.

80
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,873
Get out of there, boy.

81
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:44,918
Get with it. Hop on.

82
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:49,276
Hey, wait a minute, fellas.

83
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,873
Please.

84
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:56,470
Is something the matter?
Why are we stopping? Are we in trouble?

85
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:57,868
He is, we ain't.

86
00:11:58,040 --> 00:12:00,838
- Nice evening, fellas.
- You're a long way from home.

87
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:04,670
- I'm halfway to hell and looking for help.
- You got it, pilgrim.

88
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:08,719
You've fallen among good hands.
The Gospel says: Do unto others...

89
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:11,553
- You want a ride in?
- He can ride inside with us.

90
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:14,912
- Matthew, chapter 2, verse 3.
- Daniel, are you sure?

91
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,514
I've told you never
to question my judgment.

92
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:20,399
As I hear, I judge,
and my judgment is just.

93
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:23,996
- John, chapter 5, verse 30.
- I've never questioned your judgment.

94
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:27,630
In the 26 years of our marriage,
blessed by a devotion to the Lord...

95
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:31,076
...I have never questioned
your judgment. But I am now.

96
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:35,791
It seems ridiculous to sit in the middle
of the desert, watching men drink.

97
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:39,075
We're near halfway in.

98
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:42,034
- How about $3?
- Nope.

99
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,316
If sugar were 2 cents a barrel...

100
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:48,075
...I couldn't afford a pinch of salt
or an egg to put it on.

101
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:51,798
- I was robbed about five days back.
- Robbed? Robbed?

102
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:54,554
- Robbery, did you say?
- They nailed me on the flats.

103
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:58,595
- They took everything I had.
- Mister, you're damn lucky to be alive.

104
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:01,513
Your language is disgusting.
Both of you.

105
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:02,999
Hell, we know that.

106
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,754
Well! More profanity.

107
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:09,356
Shoot, partner, crawl on up.
You can ride for nothing.

108
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:12,592
- What do you expect me to do?
- I expect you to take action.

109
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:15,479
We should leave.
Will you please instruct the driver?

110
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:18,279
- No, thanks.
- Driver, it's getting late.

111
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:20,271
Don't fret, Your Honor.

112
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,953
We're just fixing to leave
as soon as I count my money.

113
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:27,989
- Count your what?
- Soon as I water my mule.

114
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:31,229
Watering his mule?
What on earth does he mean?

115
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,358
- I'll explain it to you later.
- How far is it to town?

116
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:37,399
- Oh, Deaddog's...
- Twenty miles.

117
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,835
- And Gila City is about...
- Same old 20 miles.

118
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,231
- I don't see any mules.
- Looks like you could use another stop.

119
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,992
Wouldn't be no good without water.

120
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,833
This stage appears to me
to be driven by horses.

121
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,399
Please.

122
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:51,994
No water between Gila and Deaddog?

123
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,513
Nope.

124
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:57,080
Sure don't seem to bother me none.

125
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:01,558
Daniel, are you going
to do something or am I?

126
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:04,518
Be worth a lot if a fella was to find it?

127
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:06,671
Worth a damn sight more than gold.

128
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:11,233
- Driver, it's getting dark.
- Generally does about this time.

129
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:15,154
- Damnedest thing I ever saw.
- Get him to start this vehicle.

130
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,515
Got enough water to hold you?

131
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:20,114
- Never, anywhere.
- Just... Daniel.

132
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:23,829
- Yep.
- I demand you start this vehicle at once.

133
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,599
Fellas?

134
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:29,995
Sure do... Well, many thanks.

135
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:34,594
- Many thanks till you're better paid.
- Start this vehicle.

136
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:37,991
I am going to report you
to your superiors.

137
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:41,068
You shall never drive again,
do you hear?

138
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:44,471
The wrath of God cometh
on the children of disobedience.

139
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:48,110
- Ephesians, chapter 5, verse 6.
- Amen.

140
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:53,715
Hallelujah, brother! The Lord
giveth and the Lord taketh away.

141
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:57,077
- Matthew, chapter 2...
- When are you coming back?

142
00:14:57,240 --> 00:15:00,676
Next week. You sure
you don't wanna ride with us?

143
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,718
No.

144
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,798
No.

145
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,191
I'll be right here, Hogue.

146
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:15,438
Right here.

147
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,397
Hey, feller.

148
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:06,718
Hey, hold up there a minute, feller.

149
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:16,316
That's 10 cents. That's my water.
My land, my water.

150
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:21,590
- Found it where it wasn't. Ten cents.
- Here's your pay.

151
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:34,994
- You shouldn't have done that.
- Is that so?

152
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:42,831
- Give me that rifle.
- I'll give you what's in it.

153
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,278
Now get out.

154
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:52,269
Drop by again.
Always open for business.

155
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,873
You're my first customer.

156
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:15,238
Appears to me you've been
17 kinds of a damn fool.

157
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,080
Not that it seems to bother you none.

158
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:41,393
Peace and goodwill, brother.
I come as a friend.

159
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:45,553
- Careful, son, I'm a man of God.
- Well, you damn near joined him.

160
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:54,200
- Anybody with you?
- I'm alone.

161
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,675
I am the Reverend
Joshua Duncan Sloane...

162
00:17:57,840 --> 00:18:01,719
...preacher to all of eastern Nevada
and selected parts of northern Arizona.

163
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,075
Well, you're a sorry preacher.

164
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,394
And a hell of a sneak.

165
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:10,155
In my case, sir, those thus attributed
often go hand in hand.

166
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:14,029
And speaking of such,
here is mine in all good fellowship.

167
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:18,551
I'm Cable Hogue.

168
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:22,156
Cable? That's rather
an unusual name, isn't it?

169
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:35,400
You have builded an oasis
out of this wilderness.

170
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:39,951
Oh, no, I just stumbled on that mud hole
over there and I dug it out a little.

171
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:44,790
You might call this place
Cable Springs. Sound good?

172
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,593
Yeah.

173
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,638
That excavation, a wine cellar perhaps?

174
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:55,475
No, that's a three-holer.
Expecting a lot of business.

175
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:02,676
I see tragedy has already struck
this cactus Eden.

176
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:04,558
No, that's no tragedy.

177
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:08,030
Shot the son of a bitch.
With his own rifle. He tried to kill me.

178
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:11,749
He was my first customer.
You're my second.

179
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:16,755
Well said and well done. Defend thyself
with the jawbone of an ass if need be.

180
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,990
You're a Good Samaritan to offer help...

181
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:22,709
...to a needy traveler...
- Hallelujah, brother. At 10 cents a head.

182
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:29,718
Water to men, sheep and hogs, 10
cents. Horses, mules and cows, 2 bits.

183
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,956
- Of course.
- In advance.

184
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:34,031
- In advance.
- In advance.

185
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:37,715
Which means before you drink,
you pay 10 cents. In advance.

186
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:41,236
Cast thy bread upon the waters,
let this man have his just needs.

187
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:46,030
You talk like a man of God, all right. But
I worked like hell for that there water.

188
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:49,715
My poor, misguided friend,
you are a sinner in need of redemption.

189
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,074
I will redeem you.

190
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:54,630
Ten cents, you pious bastard,
or I'll bury you.

191
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,477
What church did you say you was with?

192
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:42,270
The Church of the Wayfaring Stranger.
A church of my own revelation.

193
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,438
Just like that?

194
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:47,389
- Just like that.
- Where's it located?

195
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:50,199
Wherever I go, it goes with me.

196
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:55,159
Would you like to see some
of my parishioners? Sisters of the spirit.

197
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:09,635
Why, that one's naked
as a jaybird's ass.

198
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:13,395
Naked we come into this earth,
naked we shall return.

199
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:24,951
Well, well, brother Hogue.

200
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,710
I foresee a great community
springing out of the sand.

201
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:32,429
Busy thoroughfares, alabaster buildings...

202
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:35,114
...a thriving community
filled with the faithful.

203
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:38,397
- Amen.
- How much of this land is yours?

204
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,718
To sell, of course. I wish to buy.

205
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,878
Well, considerable.

206
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:46,679
I didn't see any boundary stakes
anywhere.

207
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:51,470
I suppose you've been too busy to go
into the land office and file your claim.

208
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:56,191
You know, if anyone were to drop
a word of this in Deaddog or Lizard...

209
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:59,318
...there would be 47 men
riding out here by sundown...

210
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:02,358
...with a claim in one hand
and a gun in the other.

211
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:05,557
Yes, this information could mean
quite a lot of money...

212
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:17,990
What a blessing religion must be,
preacher. It touches my heart.

213
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,957
The loan of your horse.

214
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:23,237
It's nothing, my friend.
Ride in good health with my blessing.

215
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,391
I hate to go in among them...

216
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:29,754
...but you've shown me the way
to salvation and a secured claim.

217
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:34,710
My only aim in life is to help
the misbegotten, the downtrodden...

218
00:22:35,040 --> 00:22:37,429
...and the members of my parish.

219
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,670
God bless you, preacher.

220
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:41,637
Make yourself to home.

221
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:45,713
Only don't forget, every time you take
a drink, leave 10 cents in the cup...

222
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:48,110
...or I'll blow your ass
into next Wednesday.

223
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:49,838
Come on, get up there. Get up there.

224
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:58,593
Well, get in...

225
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,877
...get it over with...

226
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:02,837
...then get out.

227
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:29,078
Please, miss.

228
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,038
Yes?

229
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:36,353
Please...

230
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:46,356
Well, hell, could you tell me
where the land office is?

231
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:49,435
Well, you're looking right at it.

232
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,115
Can't you see the sign?

233
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:56,268
Well, you see, miss, I...

234
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:03,198
Well, hell, I don't read too goddamn
good. My name's Cable Hogue.

235
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:08,192
Which one is it?

236
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,034
It's right there, with the white sign.

237
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,875
Thank you kindly, miss.

238
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:23,995
The stage office?

239
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:29,113
It's kitty-corner from here,
across from the bank.

240
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:32,158
- Thank you, miss.
- My pleasure.

241
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:34,038
Thank you truly.

242
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:19,512
How much it cost to file?

243
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:22,353
Will this be under the Desert Land Act
or homesteaded?

244
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:25,318
Well, I wanna do what's right.

245
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:29,155
Under the Desert Land Act, an individual
can file for up to 320 acres...

246
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,629
...at a dollar and a quarter an acre.

247
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,472
Plus proof of reclamation.

248
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,949
Now, whoa. Hold up there, fella.

249
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,918
What the hell does all that mean?

250
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:40,516
Land without water is not allowable.

251
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:43,319
If you can't substantiate
either agricultural...

252
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:45,789
Hold on there, fella. I got water.

253
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,313
Water?

254
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:52,196
- Where?
- West.

255
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:56,592
Eight miles through that Red Rock pass.
Off by the wagon road there.

256
00:25:57,840 --> 00:26:00,912
- Seems to be open at present, but...
- But my ass.

257
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,395
- There's no water there.
- Yeah? Come on out.

258
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:06,028
If you can't drink it,
I'll fry that claim paper.

259
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,872
Speaking of which, where is it?

260
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:10,270
All right. What's your name?

261
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,318
Cable Hogue.

262
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:15,153
C-A-B... L-E or E-L?

263
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:22,717
How do you spell Cable?

264
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:26,676
If you're bogging down on Cable,
wait till you get to Hogue.

265
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:30,389
- How much it gonna cost?
- Dollar and a quarter an acre.

266
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:33,393
Here.

267
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,078
What will that buy me?

268
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:42,029
- That will buy you two acres.
- Hang it in, then.

269
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:45,431
Let's see what it'll do,
as the lady said to the sailor.

270
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:48,752
- Two acres, Mr. Hogue?
- It's legal, ain't it?

271
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:52,197
- Well, yeah.
- Mark it.

272
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:14,999
Two acres at Cable Springs,
signed, sealed and delivered!

273
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:03,312
- You put her down right there.
- Yes, sir.

274
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:07,109
- I want a copy on my desk.
- Right away, sir.

275
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:20,751
You the boss here?

276
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:24,112
- I'm Quittner.
- Quittner?

277
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:30,236
Well, I'll bet you ain't
no quitter, are you?

278
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:41,350
So you bought yourself a claim
for two dollars and a half.

279
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:45,395
- So what?
- So it was every last cent I had.

280
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,671
I can believe it.

281
00:28:49,080 --> 00:28:51,071
Where is this claim, Mr...?

282
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:53,708
- Mr...?
- Hogue.

283
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,950
C-A-B-L-E.

284
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:59,476
- It's at Jackass Flats, about a mile...
- What you got out there...

285
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:02,393
...is so important
you gotta bother me with it?

286
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:25,111
You trying to tell me you found water
between here and Gila?

287
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,757
If you was to give me $35...

288
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:34,435
...I'd cut you in for half.

289
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:38,636
This stage line's been operating
for 35 years.

290
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:41,951
We've looked under every rock
between here and Gila.

291
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:46,272
If there was water in that 40 miles,
we'd have found it.

292
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:50,116
- I'm telling you straight!
- No, I'm telling you straight!

293
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:53,478
I've had my belly full of broken-down
prospectors, hoboes...

294
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:55,835
...and get-rich-quick-on-my-money
promoters.

295
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:59,750
Every one of you comes by here
is trying to gouge money out of me.

296
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:04,118
You're the only son of a bitch that has
the gall to pour water on my britches.

297
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:08,273
Now, I let you talk, I listened to you
and I'm not interested.

298
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:12,476
Get out and stay out, partner.

299
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:21,318
- By God, this is worth something.
- Yeah, worth two acres of Jackass Flats.

300
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:03,798
- Eleven hundred.
- Twelve.

301
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:05,393
Thirteen fifty.

302
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:08,597
- Forty, 45.
- That's 1500.

303
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:11,158
One thousand one, two...

304
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:14,233
- Ninety-two hundred.
...three, four...

305
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:17,119
...five, six...
- Twenty-five, thirty...

306
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:25,558
- Something I can do for you?
- That chunk of paper there?

307
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:28,553
That's me. Mine. Mine.

308
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:33,396
Across the street there, they think
I'm lying. They say there's no water.

309
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,232
No water?

310
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,833
Listen.

311
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:40,151
I was robbed and left to die
without a drop.

312
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:47,275
Well, do I look dead?

313
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:51,230
No, sir. Climbed up on my hind feet
and walked straight to water.

314
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,072
W-A-T-L-E.

315
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:57,349
That grabs you by the short hairs,
don't it?

316
00:31:57,520 --> 00:32:00,637
- You've got the floor.
- Those silly jackasses over there...

317
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:03,872
...can laugh at me all they want,
but they're in trouble.

318
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:06,474
Wouldn't you think
a stage line could see that?

319
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:10,599
In all the long, wrought-out,
back-breaking, kidney-shaking...

320
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:13,149
...bladder-busting
miles from here to Lizard...

321
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:16,198
...there's not one spot
of wet relief for man nor beast.

322
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:20,753
Now, if I could bring comfort to
the passengers, rest to the teams...

323
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:23,639
...food and drink to the drivers,
and water to all...

324
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:27,918
...what would be wrong with that? A
preacher out at my diggings will tell you.

325
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:30,799
- Would you doubt a man of the Gospel?
- Of course.

326
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:32,791
That's the first man I'd doubt.

327
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:36,274
By golly.

328
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:38,318
I'll be damned.

329
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:40,789
Looks like I came to the right place
after all.

330
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,516
What do you want?

331
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:47,316
Grubstake.

332
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,198
Thirty-five of them green ones.

333
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:51,510
Have you any collateral?

334
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:55,071
Do you own anything?

335
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:59,998
- Why, sure. I told you, there.
- That is $2 and a half.

336
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:23,068
Well, I'm worth something, ain't I?

337
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,990
I want to hear more.

338
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:38,349
- Why?
- Why not?

339
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:44,278
Hey, I always thought you bankers
stole for the rich.

340
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:47,989
- I didn't know you'd talk to trash like me.
- We don't steal.

341
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:51,795
Well, lend, borrow, invest
and mortgage and repossess.

342
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:54,349
What the hell else do you call it?

343
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:56,590
What's your name?

344
00:33:57,400 --> 00:33:58,913
Cable Hogue.

345
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:01,150
Cable, with an L-E.

346
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:04,392
So, Mr. Cable Hogue...

347
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:07,599
...is $35 all you want?

348
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:12,508
Will a hundred get you started?

349
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:01,472
Hey, Hildy, you got a new customer.

350
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:06,356
Go on in, mister.

351
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:09,114
She's just waiting for you.
Go on in.

352
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:12,917
Standing like a jackass eating cactus.

353
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:17,989
Yes?

354
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:22,360
Hello.

355
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:29,229
Did you want to see me?

356
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:38,350
Well, come on in.

357
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:07,189
Honey, you was smelling bad enough
to gag a dog off a gut wagon.

358
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:09,430
I smell a lot better right now though.

359
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:27,035
Hey, look at that. Inside plumbing.

360
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:30,677
As good as anything you'll find
in Kansas City.

361
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:36,759
Sweet glory, love.

362
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:40,998
Well, I had to get you rinsed off,
didn't I?

363
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:46,471
I swear I never seen a man so dirty.

364
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:49,871
You know, you must have had
a pound of dirt on you.

365
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:52,920
Well, feel a lot lighter now, Millie.

366
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:58,270
My name is Hildy.

367
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,791
Well.

368
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:12,349
Now, don't you be mixing me up
with them other ones.

369
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:17,117
Don't worry. I won't.

370
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:27,231
You know, honey...

371
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:30,840
...if you're ever thinking
of quitting this job...

372
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:33,560
...I'm building myself a place.

373
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:39,557
It's gonna be something.

374
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:42,358
No.

375
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:46,078
I've had enough of this damn desert.

376
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:49,152
Not me. Not yet.

377
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:52,036
I'm on my way up.

378
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,719
Undo me.

379
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:18,519
San Francisco is my next stop.

380
00:38:18,680 --> 00:38:20,398
San Francisco?

381
00:38:20,560 --> 00:38:24,917
- And when I hit Frisco...
- Noisy, god-awful, claptrap town.

382
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:27,959
...I'm gonna hit it in style.

383
00:38:28,120 --> 00:38:31,954
- Two days and you're tired of it.
- Tired of it?

384
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:36,073
I ain't even got there yet.

385
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:41,513
Oh, you'll get there, all right.

386
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:44,148
You bet your sweet life I will.

387
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,831
One way or another, love.

388
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:52,359
And when I do hit Frisco...

389
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:56,035
...I'm gonna be the ladiest damn lady
you ever seen.

390
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:09,757
I'm gonna marry me the richest man
in San Francisco.

391
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:15,234
Maybe the two richest men.
It's just a question of time.

392
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,631
Well, if you ever need any help...

393
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:24,115
- You remember my name?
- You remember mine?

394
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:35,149
Come here.

395
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:45,153
God's pure and natural elements
are being threatened by the devil, yes.

396
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,597
Sinners.

397
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,876
What's wrong?

398
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:56,197
The devil seeks to destroy you
with machines!

399
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:59,108
Ask me how I know.

400
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:04,434
There are those of us who talk to God.
God talked to me the other day.

401
00:40:04,800 --> 00:40:06,756
He said:

402
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:11,917
"Inventions are the work of Satan.

403
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:15,352
Tell them how it is, James."

404
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:19,953
I gotta go. That pious son of a bitch
could have sold me out.

405
00:40:20,120 --> 00:40:23,999
- What?
- Taking the stage to Gila. Sold me out.

406
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:26,071
Hogue.

407
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:28,675
Hogue.

408
00:40:30,440 --> 00:40:32,351
- Come here.
- "Turn your backs.

409
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:35,990
And gather by the river
with me, James."

410
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:39,434
That's what the Almighty said.

411
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:44,268
Lost it. No good.

412
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:51,673
Trouble is, I... I forgot
to mark my boundaries.

413
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:53,993
Build me a claim monument.

414
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:58,039
- What in the hell are you talking about?
- Just know it.

415
00:40:58,200 --> 00:41:00,316
- Bother me.
- Bother you?

416
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:02,990
All the way through it.

417
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:10,590
Keep thinking of that damn preacher
out there.

418
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:13,558
- Maybe come here to cheat me.
- Hogue.

419
00:41:13,720 --> 00:41:16,439
Hell of a time to hold a goddamn
prayer meeting!

420
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:19,512
What is the matter with you?

421
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:23,157
Hey!

422
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:24,548
What?

423
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:27,473
- Ain't you forgetting something?
- What?

424
00:41:28,240 --> 00:41:31,152
Well, what about me?

425
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:34,949
- Me. Me and my money.
- Money?

426
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:38,109
For what?

427
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,875
Well, if you don't want me here.

428
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:57,473
Easy. Easy.

429
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:02,191
Whoa, hold up there, now. Careful.

430
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:07,797
- Didn't take you long, mister.
- Just a damn minute.

431
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:12,238
Hildy, listen to me. I told you.
He's gonna take the stage to Gila.

432
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:14,391
Sold me out.

433
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:18,276
- I'll be back.
- Back, hell. You'll pay me now!

434
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:23,076
Look at him go!
Where's he going?

435
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:27,550
Attagirl, Hildy.

436
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:36,914
- There you are, you son of a bitch.
- I told you I'd be back.

437
00:42:37,240 --> 00:42:40,152
- You call yourself a man?
- Well, of course I do.

438
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:43,630
- I got business at the springs.
- You got business with me.

439
00:42:44,120 --> 00:42:46,031
Now, get up here and settle up.

440
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:47,997
- Later, Hildy.
- Later, hell!

441
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:53,235
Well, you know how it is, folks. Women.

442
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:02,715
Just a damn minute, Cable!

443
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:17,873
- Peace. Everything will be all right.
- Take your hands off of me.

444
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:21,271
- Not you. You!
- Will you get off my face?

445
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:24,159
Is that you, Robert?
What are you doing?

446
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:35,154
Get ahold of him, Frank.
He's getting away.

447
00:43:35,320 --> 00:43:37,231
Get him! Get him!

448
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:41,114
Go get him, Frank!

449
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:49,628
Nasty man, we'll never see you again.

450
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:52,951
- Hope he breaks his neck.
- Get the hell out of here!

451
00:43:57,520 --> 00:44:02,071
- Come on, let's ride him out of here!
- Why, you son of a bitch.

452
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:04,152
It's all right, folks.

453
00:44:04,320 --> 00:44:05,799
Yeah, it's all right.

454
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:11,475
Hey, come back here!

455
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:14,234
Cable Hogue, you're no damn good!

456
00:44:14,400 --> 00:44:17,312
- I'll be back!
- You aren't either!

457
00:44:21,080 --> 00:44:23,310
You hussy!

458
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:58,399
Welcome back to the fold, brother.

459
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:08,831
Drink up, preacher.

460
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:13,152
Gonna get spruced up.
Going back in amongst them.

461
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:16,273
I got unfinished business in Deaddog.

462
00:45:17,200 --> 00:45:19,509
Amen.

463
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:20,110
Thank you.

464
00:46:21,680 --> 00:46:23,989
That collar comes off as easy
as it goes on.

465
00:46:24,160 --> 00:46:28,915
Of course. If I cannot rouse heaven,
I intend to raise hell.

466
00:47:00,600 --> 00:47:02,636
You see?

467
00:47:02,800 --> 00:47:06,475
I told you. Went clean through.

468
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:09,873
She took her.

469
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:23,189
Children, we are gathered here under
the sight of the Lord Almighty...

470
00:47:23,360 --> 00:47:25,715
Not now, Josh.

471
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:29,754
Hildy...

472
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:11,674
Now, Josh.

473
00:48:11,840 --> 00:48:17,119
Children, we are gathered here under
the sight of the Lord Almighty...

474
00:48:38,760 --> 00:48:42,196
Cable Hogue, take off your damn boots.

475
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:47,149
Now, that's better.

476
00:48:57,280 --> 00:49:00,192
Well, the Lord giveth
and the Lord taketh away.

477
00:49:11,640 --> 00:49:13,278
Good evening.

478
00:49:26,680 --> 00:49:29,069
Just passing through.

479
00:51:32,360 --> 00:51:33,713
Yes?

480
00:51:37,240 --> 00:51:40,596
My apologies for intruding
in your time of obvious grief...

481
00:51:41,040 --> 00:51:44,237
...but being a man of the cloth
I could not pass your door...

482
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:48,109
...without at least offering you
the solace of my services.

483
00:51:57,000 --> 00:51:59,958
I am Reverend
Joshua Duncan Sloane.

484
00:52:00,560 --> 00:52:03,199
Reverend, thank you for coming.

485
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:20,437
Come, child, take my hand.

486
00:52:28,920 --> 00:52:30,717
The Lord works in many ways.

487
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:36,036
Sometimes, when he has dealt too much
for one to bear...

488
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:38,998
...he sends a messenger
to comfort and love.

489
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:42,798
- He does?
- Yes.

490
00:52:43,960 --> 00:52:46,190
Such a messenger am I.

491
00:52:47,280 --> 00:52:51,478
