01:16:12,080 --> 01:16:14,116
Morning, Preacher Sloane.

734
01:16:14,640 --> 01:16:16,153
Good morning, Hildy.

735
01:16:50,640 --> 01:16:53,279
- Can I help you, mister?
- Yeah, whose horse is that?

736
01:16:53,440 --> 01:16:55,829
- Which one?
- The one that's all lathered up.

737
01:16:56,000 --> 01:16:57,638
Oh, that.

738
01:16:58,680 --> 01:17:00,318
That's mine.

739
01:17:02,080 --> 01:17:06,596
- What's its name?
- That? That's...

740
01:17:07,320 --> 01:17:08,514
Old Alexander.

741
01:17:08,680 --> 01:17:11,433
I will protect you.
The violence might spread inside.

742
01:17:11,600 --> 01:17:14,353
Joshua, what the hell
do you think you're doing?

743
01:17:16,040 --> 01:17:17,314
Funny name for a mare.

744
01:17:18,320 --> 01:17:20,197
Well...

745
01:17:20,360 --> 01:17:24,592
...like the lady said to the sailor,
it all depends on how you look at it.

746
01:17:25,400 --> 01:17:28,676
Yea, I will protect you as a shepherd
protects his flock.

747
01:17:28,840 --> 01:17:31,308
Yeah, well, I heard about
them sheepherders...

748
01:17:31,480 --> 01:17:34,074
...and you ain't sticking my feet
in your boots.

749
01:17:34,240 --> 01:17:37,073
You listen to me.
I want that son of a bitch.

750
01:17:37,240 --> 01:17:40,915
I'll pay a hundred dollars in gold,
wet or dry, dead or alive.

751
01:17:41,080 --> 01:17:42,877
A hundred dollars?

752
01:17:44,160 --> 01:17:46,469
- If I see him, you'll get him.
- I better.

753
01:17:46,640 --> 01:17:48,232
So long, fella.

754
01:17:48,400 --> 01:17:50,834
- Don't forget.
- I won't.

755
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:53,116
You better not.

756
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:58,318
Preacher! I told you to stay
the hell out of there!

757
01:18:02,240 --> 01:18:05,630
Thank you, Cable, for sanctuary.

758
01:18:07,080 --> 01:18:10,755
- My dear, this smells delicious.
- Thank you, Joshua.

759
01:18:11,800 --> 01:18:14,394
- It is good.
- Hold up there, preacher.

760
01:18:14,560 --> 01:18:17,597
- That'll be 50 cents.
- Oh, that's hardly fair.

761
01:18:17,880 --> 01:18:21,839
- Not fair? He should pay me double.
- Why? You haven't charged me nothing.

762
01:18:22,040 --> 01:18:24,679
That's because you
haven't charged me nothing.

763
01:18:28,760 --> 01:18:31,320
Oh, brother, you really are
a true Samaritan.

764
01:18:31,880 --> 01:18:33,711
Don't push your luck, Josh.

765
01:18:44,760 --> 01:18:47,832
- Wouldn't you like to say grace?
- Not over my food.

766
01:18:48,680 --> 01:18:50,716
Very well, then, I'll say grace.

767
01:19:06,560 --> 01:19:09,916
Dear Lord, we thank thee
for all this good food...

768
01:19:10,080 --> 01:19:12,640
...and that we can share it as one.

769
01:19:12,800 --> 01:19:15,030
We thank thee for thy goodness
and thy mercy.

770
01:19:15,480 --> 01:19:17,789
Bless this food, O Lord...

771
01:19:23,320 --> 01:19:24,753
And bless this house.

772
01:19:29,280 --> 01:19:31,669
- Amen.
- Amen.

773
01:19:32,080 --> 01:19:33,513
Amen.

774
01:19:36,400 --> 01:19:37,549
Thank you, Hildy.

775
01:19:40,280 --> 01:19:41,793
Hogue...

776
01:19:44,320 --> 01:19:46,914
...I'll be leaving tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?

777
01:19:47,080 --> 01:19:51,232
You knew I was only gonna stay
one day, maybe two.

778
01:19:51,720 --> 01:19:54,359
It's been over three weeks already.

779
01:19:54,520 --> 01:19:57,717
- It can't be.
- Has, though.

780
01:20:01,600 --> 01:20:04,717
Guess I got used to your cooking and all.

781
01:20:08,600 --> 01:20:11,068
It has been nice hearing you sing.

782
01:20:21,840 --> 01:20:25,753
I admit, I thought a lot about staying.

783
01:20:30,520 --> 01:20:33,512
You treated me like a real lady, Hogue.

784
01:20:34,760 --> 01:20:36,751
You were good to me.

785
01:20:42,360 --> 01:20:43,793
Not good enough?

786
01:20:48,440 --> 01:20:51,079
Maybe too good, I don't know.

787
01:20:52,920 --> 01:20:55,070
I just can't handle it.

788
01:21:00,960 --> 01:21:04,191
Thank you very much for everything,
but I'm leaving.

789
01:21:04,840 --> 01:21:06,592
Excuse me.

790
01:21:11,640 --> 01:21:13,790
Sort of lost my appetite.

791
01:21:15,320 --> 01:21:18,278
I better find you
a place to sleep, preacher.

792
01:21:19,360 --> 01:21:20,998
No need.

793
01:21:26,040 --> 01:21:29,316
That bed in there will suit me
just fine and dandy.

794
01:21:29,760 --> 01:21:33,469
It's fine and dandy, but it ain't yours.

795
01:21:33,640 --> 01:21:37,030
Well, isn't a guest
entitled to bed and board?

796
01:21:37,200 --> 01:21:38,394
A paying guest.

797
01:21:38,560 --> 01:21:41,552
Oh, stop it. Both of you
gonna sleep outside tonight.

798
01:21:47,200 --> 01:21:49,077
Outside, both of you.

799
01:22:30,720 --> 01:22:33,518
- Good night, Cable.
- Good night, Josh.

800
01:23:44,720 --> 01:23:47,712
Morning, brother Hogue.
Sleep well last night?

801
01:23:47,880 --> 01:23:49,359
Nope.

802
01:23:53,720 --> 01:23:56,473
- Is Hildy up yet?
- Left early.

803
01:23:57,400 --> 01:24:00,392
- How do you know?
- Well, you know how it is, Josh.

804
01:24:11,800 --> 01:24:13,358
Funny thing...

805
01:24:15,440 --> 01:24:19,399
...it doesn't matter how much
or how little you've wandered around...

806
01:24:19,560 --> 01:24:21,790
...how many women you've been with.

807
01:24:22,840 --> 01:24:24,990
Every once in awhile, one of them...

808
01:24:25,160 --> 01:24:27,720
...cuts right through.

809
01:24:28,240 --> 01:24:29,673
Right straight into you.

810
01:24:37,760 --> 01:24:39,716
What do you do about it?

811
01:24:42,440 --> 01:24:46,911
I suppose maybe when you die
you get over it.

812
01:24:49,520 --> 01:24:51,238
So long, Cable.

813
01:24:54,240 --> 01:24:56,037
So long, Josh.

814
01:25:47,000 --> 01:25:48,911
It's me!

815
01:25:49,080 --> 01:25:51,071
Cable Hogue!

816
01:25:51,960 --> 01:25:53,951
Right here!

817
01:25:56,600 --> 01:25:58,113
Waiting.

818
01:26:03,800 --> 01:26:08,510
Right here! Waiting!

819
01:26:29,560 --> 01:26:32,518
Come on, boy. Get with it.

820
01:26:44,120 --> 01:26:47,396
Come on, Blackie! Get in.

821
01:26:53,240 --> 01:26:54,434
Get in there, boy.

822
01:26:59,200 --> 01:27:00,918
Whoa, boy.

823
01:27:01,480 --> 01:27:04,950
Don't feed them, we're just staying
long enough to water the horses.

824
01:27:05,160 --> 01:27:07,720
- And we're running late.
- All right, Ben.

825
01:27:21,320 --> 01:27:23,390
Welcome to Cable Springs.

826
01:27:28,960 --> 01:27:30,837
It's out in the back, ma'am.

827
01:27:31,880 --> 01:27:36,032
I was wondering and worrying if you got
out of there all right. Glad you made it.

828
01:27:37,240 --> 01:27:39,754
Howdy, Cable.

829
01:27:40,440 --> 01:27:41,589
Hogue.

830
01:27:41,760 --> 01:27:45,912
Come on and have a drink of the
best damn water for 50 mile around.

831
01:27:46,080 --> 01:27:48,036
I found it where it wasn't.

832
01:28:14,360 --> 01:28:17,955
- How long you had this place?
- Three years and a half.

833
01:28:18,200 --> 01:28:19,474
Pretty big layout.

834
01:28:21,280 --> 01:28:23,555
Well, I owe it all to you boys.

835
01:28:24,920 --> 01:28:29,471
When I come out of there, I found this
water hole and just went into business.

836
01:28:33,560 --> 01:28:35,551
Looks like you done real well.

837
01:28:37,000 --> 01:28:39,309
Big, fat bankbook, huh, Cable?

838
01:28:39,480 --> 01:28:42,756
Hogue in a bank?
You don't know him better than that...

839
01:28:42,920 --> 01:28:44,478
...you don't know him at all.

840
01:28:44,640 --> 01:28:46,312
Here you go, Cable.

841
01:28:46,480 --> 01:28:48,869
Another month paid in full.

842
01:28:49,240 --> 01:28:51,515
No, no banks for me.

843
01:28:51,680 --> 01:28:55,468
I'll just put this in the old sock,
and I got it well hid.

844
01:28:56,720 --> 01:29:00,633
- We're glad to hear you're doing so well.
- If I was doing half as good...

845
01:29:00,800 --> 01:29:04,429
...I'd be a rich son of a bitch
instead of just a poor one.

846
01:29:04,720 --> 01:29:08,599
All right, folks, let's go!
All aboard for Deaddog!

847
01:29:08,760 --> 01:29:11,149
Well, I owe it all to you boys.

848
01:29:13,160 --> 01:29:15,993
Now, you come back
and see me, now, you hear?

849
01:29:16,160 --> 01:29:18,435
- We will.
- One of these days.

850
01:29:18,600 --> 01:29:20,511
Now, you can count on it.

851
01:29:32,720 --> 01:29:36,838
Blackie, get out of there. Come on, boy.

852
01:29:37,200 --> 01:29:39,156
Get out of there.

853
01:29:39,320 --> 01:29:41,151
- See you, Hogue.
- So long, Ben.

854
01:29:52,920 --> 01:29:57,550
<i>Taggart and Bowen</i>
<i>As quick as you please</i>

855
01:29:57,720 --> 01:30:01,713
<i>Took all the money and left for the trees</i>

856
01:30:10,720 --> 01:30:12,836
Hey, Cable?

857
01:30:13,000 --> 01:30:15,434
We come for that visit.

858
01:30:15,600 --> 01:30:17,318
Cable!

859
01:30:19,160 --> 01:30:21,469
I don't think he's here.

860
01:30:23,720 --> 01:30:26,188
No, I don't think he is.

861
01:30:26,360 --> 01:30:28,032
You check inside.

862
01:30:31,120 --> 01:30:33,031
Come on, get up there.

863
01:30:38,440 --> 01:30:41,238
We'll drink all your water, Cable.

864
01:30:41,400 --> 01:30:44,039
<i>We'll drink your well dry</i>

865
01:30:45,320 --> 01:30:48,790
<i>Water goes good with a bottle of rye</i>

866
01:32:02,200 --> 01:32:04,430
Bowen. Bowen!

867
01:32:09,280 --> 01:32:11,794
Just lookie what we got here.

868
01:32:25,680 --> 01:32:27,557
Another one.

869
01:32:30,040 --> 01:32:31,917
What do you think?

870
01:32:32,080 --> 01:32:34,230
Well, we found the copper.

871
01:32:34,680 --> 01:32:37,353
Gold and silver gotta be next.

872
01:32:37,760 --> 01:32:40,399
Why in hell don't we just wait
till he comes back?

873
01:32:40,560 --> 01:32:43,996
- Let him do the digging?
- Suits me, boys.

874
01:32:49,600 --> 01:32:51,477
- You heard that.
- Shut up.

875
01:32:51,800 --> 01:32:53,392
Come on out.

876
01:32:55,800 --> 01:32:58,234
With your hands up, fellas.

877
01:32:58,400 --> 01:32:59,799
Think it over.

878
01:33:00,680 --> 01:33:02,796
I got lots of time.

879
01:33:04,360 --> 01:33:05,554
What's he doing?

880
01:33:05,720 --> 01:33:09,599
Well, I ain't gonna poke my head
over the edge to find out.

881
01:33:11,040 --> 01:33:12,268
Hogue?

882
01:33:12,480 --> 01:33:15,074
You know you ain't got no guts.

883
01:33:15,560 --> 01:33:19,633
Why, last time you had a gun on us
you didn't use it.

884
01:33:19,800 --> 01:33:22,439
Yeah, now, of course that's a fact.

885
01:33:23,000 --> 01:33:24,991
You said I was yellow.

886
01:33:26,960 --> 01:33:28,951
Wanna try your luck again?

887
01:33:29,680 --> 01:33:31,432
- He's bluffing.
- Yeah, yeah.

888
01:33:31,600 --> 01:33:33,955
Sun's kind of hot, ain't it, fellas?

889
01:33:34,120 --> 01:33:37,078
Of course you could enjoy it
if you had plenty of water.

890
01:33:37,440 --> 01:33:40,591
And that's what I got, plenty of water.

891
01:33:41,600 --> 01:33:45,479
- Get over. Right up there.
- Right there.

892
01:33:45,640 --> 01:33:48,234
I ain't running this time, fellas.

893
01:33:48,400 --> 01:33:50,231
- Staying right here.
- Your gun.

894
01:33:50,400 --> 01:33:55,758
- Sooner or later you gotta come out.
- Three count. Ready? Ready?

895
01:33:56,640 --> 01:33:59,518
One, two...

896
01:33:59,680 --> 01:34:01,113
...now!

897
01:34:08,800 --> 01:34:12,793
- We got him.
- He might still be alive.

898
01:34:13,360 --> 01:34:14,918
Take a look.

899
01:34:16,040 --> 01:34:19,510
- You're sure?
- Damn it, take a look.

900
01:34:21,560 --> 01:34:23,516
Give me a boost.

901
01:34:24,280 --> 01:34:26,510
Easy and up we go.

902
01:34:27,760 --> 01:34:30,115
Little higher, Taggart.

903
01:34:30,680 --> 01:34:33,558
- Get up there.
- No. Just easy.

904
01:34:33,720 --> 01:34:34,994
Easy.

905
01:34:38,320 --> 01:34:42,438
Put me down.
Put me down, damn it, down!

906
01:34:42,600 --> 01:34:44,909
- We never touched him.
- Where is he?

907
01:34:45,080 --> 01:34:48,470
Well, why in the hell
don't you take a look?

908
01:34:53,400 --> 01:34:55,197
Now what's he up to?

909
01:35:02,200 --> 01:35:03,519
Hey, Taggart.

910
01:35:05,920 --> 01:35:08,912
Oh, my God. Taggart, help me.

911
01:35:09,680 --> 01:35:12,274
Hey. Hey!

912
01:35:12,440 --> 01:35:13,759
- Hey, Taggart.
- Oh, my God.

913
01:35:13,960 --> 01:35:16,428
Hey! Taggart!

914
01:35:18,640 --> 01:35:21,871
Taggart. Son of a bitch, Taggart.
Please, Taggart.

915
01:35:26,280 --> 01:35:27,599
God.

916
01:35:27,760 --> 01:35:30,228
- Taggart, I'm leaving this place.
- Not without me.

917
01:35:30,920 --> 01:35:33,150
Hold up there, boys.

918
01:35:38,920 --> 01:35:41,832
Now, you can start taking off your duds.

919
01:35:43,520 --> 01:35:45,112
Get them off.

920
01:35:50,520 --> 01:35:52,511
Keep your underwear, that's all.

921
01:36:01,200 --> 01:36:03,316
And your boots, get them off.

922
01:36:04,320 --> 01:36:05,673
Boots.

923
01:36:09,000 --> 01:36:11,833
- Socks too.
- Socks?

924
01:36:16,120 --> 01:36:17,599
Now...

925
01:36:18,840 --> 01:36:22,116
...you're gonna head back out
through them hills.

926
01:36:22,800 --> 01:36:25,872
Because if I catch you on a road,
I'm gonna kill you.

927
01:36:26,040 --> 01:36:28,508
But there's no water.

928
01:36:29,080 --> 01:36:32,277
And don't that sound familiar?

929
01:36:32,440 --> 01:36:34,396
I ain't going.

930
01:36:57,760 --> 01:37:00,832
You ain't got the guts, Hogue.

931
01:37:50,360 --> 01:37:52,351
No. No, no.

932
01:37:52,520 --> 01:37:54,078
No, Cable.

933
01:37:54,240 --> 01:37:55,673
No.

934
01:38:00,600 --> 01:38:02,670
Hey, what's that?

935
01:38:02,840 --> 01:38:04,637
- What?
- That.

936
01:38:07,160 --> 01:38:09,435
I seen one once before.

937
01:38:09,600 --> 01:38:13,798
- Out here, on them roads?
- It go anywhere.

938
01:38:18,120 --> 01:38:21,271
Help! Help!

939
01:38:21,440 --> 01:38:23,317
He's gonna kill me!

940
01:38:23,480 --> 01:38:24,913
Kill me!

941
01:38:25,080 --> 01:38:26,274
Stop!

942
01:38:26,440 --> 01:38:27,953
Stop!

943
01:38:30,240 --> 01:38:35,439
You damn, dumb, dumb bastards.

944
01:38:38,120 --> 01:38:41,078
Horseless carriage.
Don't look that good to me.

945
01:38:48,920 --> 01:38:50,831
Went right on by.

946
01:39:00,920 --> 01:39:02,353
Well...

947
01:39:03,480 --> 01:39:06,199
...that's gonna be
the next fella's worry.

948
01:39:45,200 --> 01:39:50,354
I can't go it out there, Cable.

949
01:39:51,640 --> 01:39:53,710
- That right?
- It wasn't my fault.

950
01:39:53,880 --> 01:39:56,599
All I did was...

951
01:40:00,760 --> 01:40:03,479
I'm sorry, Cable.

952
01:40:06,280 --> 01:40:09,875
You know how it was with Taggart.

953
01:40:10,520 --> 01:40:13,353
Yeah, I know.

954
01:40:15,040 --> 01:40:16,792
Bury him.

955
01:40:16,960 --> 01:40:18,678
Bury him.

956
01:41:20,040 --> 01:41:21,996
He's under.

957
01:41:22,840 --> 01:41:24,478
Good.

958
01:41:25,760 --> 01:41:29,230
What else would you like me to do?

959
01:41:45,240 --> 01:41:47,310
What kind of a cockeyed
schedule is this?

960
01:41:47,480 --> 01:41:50,517
Ain't got no passengers,
just two, three sacks of mail.

961
01:41:50,680 --> 01:41:53,353
Well, it don't matter really.
I'm leaving.

962
01:41:53,520 --> 01:41:55,636
- Leaving?
- You leaving the desert?

963
01:41:55,800 --> 01:41:58,394
It's a big world, fellas.
I wanna see some of it.

964
01:41:58,560 --> 01:42:00,118
Next stop, San Francisco.

965
01:42:00,280 --> 01:42:01,508
You serious?

966
01:42:01,680 --> 01:42:04,114
So you're really going in
amongst them, Hogue?

967
01:42:04,280 --> 01:42:06,191
- Shoot, that ain't like you.
- Ain't it?

968
01:42:06,360 --> 01:42:08,669
- You just watch me.
- He means it.

969
01:42:08,840 --> 01:42:11,718
- You bet I mean it.
- Now, hold on.

970
01:42:11,880 --> 01:42:14,440
You just can't up and leave
the station like this.

971
01:42:14,600 --> 01:42:18,115
Well, what are we gonna do
between Deaddog and Lizard?

972
01:42:24,040 --> 01:42:28,830
Gentlemen, I'd like you
to meet my former partner...

973
01:42:29,000 --> 01:42:31,070
...Samuel D. Bowen.

974
01:42:34,520 --> 01:42:36,590
Hey, get some clothes on.

975
01:42:36,760 --> 01:42:38,352
Yes, sir.

976
01:42:38,800 --> 01:42:40,438
Now, wait a minute.

977
01:42:40,600 --> 01:42:42,989
- You can't leave some fool...
- Samuel D. Bowen!

978
01:42:43,160 --> 01:42:46,516
...running around in his long johns
in charge here.

979
01:42:47,520 --> 01:42:49,590
My God, what's that?

980
01:42:51,360 --> 01:42:54,158
Ugly-Iooking damn thing, ain't it?

981
01:43:01,800 --> 01:43:06,032
Kind of strange, moving all by itself.

982
01:43:06,200 --> 01:43:08,430
I seen two before.

983
01:43:49,040 --> 01:43:52,271
That there lady is Hildy.

984
01:43:53,240 --> 01:43:54,832
Hi, Hogue.

985
01:43:55,400 --> 01:43:58,358
The ladiest damn lady I ever saw.

986
01:44:25,720 --> 01:44:27,392
I beg your pardon, sir.

987
01:44:28,200 --> 01:44:32,273
- Might I borrow a tank of water?
- No.

988
01:44:32,440 --> 01:44:35,000
No, no.

989
01:44:35,800 --> 01:44:39,156
Mr. Cable Hogue don't
let nobody borrow nothing.

990
01:44:54,520 --> 01:44:55,953
Hey, Cable?

991
01:45:03,000 --> 01:45:04,752
Cable.

992
01:45:06,440 --> 01:45:09,238
How much water you think
this thing will take?

993
01:45:09,400 --> 01:45:11,152
Three, maybe four horses' worth?

994
01:45:11,320 --> 01:45:15,313
Well, how the hell would I know?
You're in charge here, Bowen.

995
01:45:17,400 --> 01:45:22,599
That'll be five horses' worth,
not a cent less.

996
01:45:22,760 --> 01:45:26,275
Pull it up on the rise
and help me fetch the water.

997
01:45:40,240 --> 01:45:41,992
Get that damn thing out of here...

998
01:45:42,160 --> 01:45:45,357
...before my team takes a notion
to tromp the hell out of it.

999
01:45:48,760 --> 01:45:52,036
Hildy, you do look fine.

1000
01:45:52,200 --> 01:45:57,797
I guess you found one of those rich
husbands you was always looking for.

1001
01:45:58,640 --> 01:46:01,234
Well, let's just put it
this way, Hogue.

1002
01:46:01,400 --> 01:46:03,630
I ain't hurting no more.

1003
01:46:07,640 --> 01:46:11,315
I was just headed for New Orleans.

1004
01:46:13,720 --> 01:46:17,713
I stopped by to check
to see if maybe you was ready.

1005
01:46:19,320 --> 01:46:20,958
I'm ready.

1006
01:46:22,040 --> 01:46:24,793
You'd leave your desert, Hogue?

1007
01:46:24,960 --> 01:46:27,474
Hell, I've already gone, honey.

1008
01:46:33,800 --> 01:46:35,392
I'll go get ready.

1009
01:46:35,560 --> 01:46:37,915
I'll be back in a minute.

1010
01:46:40,600 --> 01:46:43,637
We got nothing but time, Hogue...

1011
01:46:43,800 --> 01:46:46,030
...nothing but time.

1012
01:46:48,800 --> 01:46:52,839
Hey, fellas, I'm headed
for New Orleans, in style.

1013
01:46:53,000 --> 01:46:55,878
By God, I wish
I was going with you.

1014
01:47:05,360 --> 01:47:06,679
Hey.

1015
01:47:12,480 --> 01:47:14,994
I seen two before.

1016
01:47:17,560 --> 01:47:21,473
I guess you need the water
for the steam, huh?

1017
01:47:21,640 --> 01:47:25,918
- No. It burns gasoline.
- Oh, yeah, burns it. Yeah.

1018
01:47:26,080 --> 01:47:30,198
Did you hear that, Cable?
It burns gasoline.

1019
01:47:30,360 --> 01:47:32,430
Well, of course it does.

1020
01:47:32,600 --> 01:47:37,276
You know, maybe a fella could pick up
some extra money selling that too.

1021
01:47:37,440 --> 01:47:39,829
That gasoline.

1022
01:47:41,960 --> 01:47:45,794
Mister, that'll cost you 10 cents more.

1023
01:47:46,840 --> 01:47:48,432
Hey, Bowen.

1024
01:47:51,320 --> 01:47:53,436
- Hogue, watch out.
- Hold it.

1025
01:47:53,640 --> 01:47:55,153
Hold it.

1026
01:48:00,280 --> 01:48:02,350
Oh, my God. Hogue?

1027
01:48:08,440 --> 01:48:11,477
Son of a bitch
kicks worse than a mule.

1028
01:48:12,800 --> 01:48:16,315
- You hurt, Cable?
- Hell, I'm all right.

1029
01:48:17,760 --> 01:48:20,035
No, I'm not.

1030
01:48:21,560 --> 01:48:25,872
Hell, Hogue. It's a long ways
from your heart and on the wrong side.

1031
01:48:38,120 --> 01:48:39,473
Well, thanks, fellas.

1032
01:48:39,640 --> 01:48:41,949
Much better out here.

1033
01:48:58,680 --> 01:49:00,193
Josh.

1034
01:49:00,760 --> 01:49:03,320
Well, well, brother Hogue.

1035
01:49:03,480 --> 01:49:04,913
What's all this?

1036
01:49:05,400 --> 01:49:07,630
What in the hell is that?

1037
01:49:07,800 --> 01:49:09,870
Just a means of transportation.

1038
01:49:10,040 --> 01:49:13,510
- Well, it sure is an ugly thing.
- You don't look so good, Cable.

1039
01:49:13,680 --> 01:49:17,070
- Are you in trouble?
- No trouble, just dying. Last reckoning.

1040
01:49:17,240 --> 01:49:20,038
Well, it comes to us all.
Prepare yourself, Cable.

1041
01:49:20,200 --> 01:49:24,034
Oh, shut up, Joshua. It ain't so.

1042
01:49:24,200 --> 01:49:26,077
You'll be up and around in no time.

1043
01:49:26,240 --> 01:49:28,595
- Cable?
- Yep.

1044
01:49:28,760 --> 01:49:30,751
I wanna thank you
for what you've done.

1045
01:49:31,360 --> 01:49:35,035
And here I waited three years
to get even with you.

1046
01:49:35,200 --> 01:49:37,430
I was gonna piss on your grave.

1047
01:49:43,800 --> 01:49:48,590
Boys, when I go just bury me where
the sand's soft and the digging's easy.

1048
01:49:48,760 --> 01:49:51,638
Oh, hush, Cable.
You're gonna be just fine.

1049
01:49:51,800 --> 01:49:55,156
Hildy. That man you was married to...

1050
01:49:57,320 --> 01:50:01,393
He died about a month back
of a stroke, in bed.

1051
01:50:03,800 --> 01:50:05,870
But he died happy.

1052
01:50:08,680 --> 01:50:10,193
I'll just bet he did.

1053
01:50:10,360 --> 01:50:14,751
As a matter of fact, if you gents would
be kind enough to move me inside...

1054
01:50:14,920 --> 01:50:18,230
...I'd kind of like to throw a little...
- Oh, Cable Hogue.

1055
01:50:18,400 --> 01:50:20,277
- Hang in there.
- Brother Hogue...

1056
01:50:20,440 --> 01:50:24,956
...this is a time for deep and serious
reflection, not of base and vile lust.

1057
01:50:27,200 --> 01:50:30,033
Josh, it's about time
you earned your keep.

1058
01:50:30,720 --> 01:50:34,269
- Preach me a funeral sermon.
- Oh, for heaven's sake.

1059
01:50:34,840 --> 01:50:39,470
A good one. Don't make me out no
saint, but don't put me down too deep.

1060
01:50:39,640 --> 01:50:41,949
- You mean now?
- Yeah.

1061
01:50:42,120 --> 01:50:44,475
It's not so much the dying
that you hate...

1062
01:50:44,640 --> 01:50:47,916
...it's not knowing what they're
gonna say about you, that's all.

1063
01:50:48,080 --> 01:50:51,595
Now, all my life I've been
scared of this living.

1064
01:50:51,760 --> 01:50:53,478
Now...

1065
01:50:54,160 --> 01:50:56,310
...gotta do the other.

1066
01:50:58,520 --> 01:51:00,829
Well, come on, now,
I can't wait all day.

1067
01:51:01,000 --> 01:51:02,877
I ain't got any time.

1068
01:51:03,040 --> 01:51:06,191
- Brethren!
- Bull's eye! See?

1069
01:51:06,360 --> 01:51:09,716
We are gathered here...

1070
01:51:11,480 --> 01:51:14,631
...in the sight of God and all his glory...

1071
01:51:14,800 --> 01:51:19,191
...to lay to rest Cable Hogue.
- Cable Hogue. Amen to that.

1072
01:51:20,080 --> 01:51:25,438
Now, most funeral orations,
Lord, lie about a man.

1073
01:51:25,960 --> 01:51:29,635
Compare him to the angels,
whitewash him with a really wide brush.

1074
01:51:29,800 --> 01:51:33,554
But, you know, Lord,
and I know that it just is not true.

1075
01:51:33,720 --> 01:51:34,948
Hang in there, preacher.

1076
01:51:35,120 --> 01:51:38,715
Now, a man is made out of bad
as well as good, all of us.

1077
01:51:38,880 --> 01:51:43,078
Cable Hogue was born into this world,
nobody knows when or where.

1078
01:51:43,240 --> 01:51:46,676
He came stumbling out of the
wilderness like a prophet of old.

1079
01:51:46,840 --> 01:51:48,273
Sounds right, is right.

1080
01:51:48,440 --> 01:51:52,194
Out of the barren wastes
he carved himself a one-man kingdom.

1081
01:51:52,360 --> 01:51:54,715
- I don't know.
- Some said he was ruthless.

1082
01:51:54,880 --> 01:51:57,713
- Who said that?
- More than one, Hogue.

1083
01:51:57,880 --> 01:52:00,269
But you could do worse, Lord...

1084
01:52:00,440 --> 01:52:04,718
...than to take to your bosom
Cable Hogue.

1085
01:52:04,880 --> 01:52:09,078
He wasn't really a good man,
he wasn't a bad man.

1086
01:52:10,040 --> 01:52:12,349
But, Lord, he was a man.

1087
01:52:13,040 --> 01:52:15,270
Amen to that.

1088
01:52:17,280 --> 01:52:19,475
He charged too much...

1089
01:52:21,240 --> 01:52:23,754
...he was as stingy as they come.

1090
01:52:23,920 --> 01:52:28,277
Yes, he might have cheated,
but he was square about it.

1091
01:52:28,440 --> 01:52:31,716
Rich or poor,
he gouged them all the same.

1092
01:52:31,880 --> 01:52:33,871
When Cable Hogue died...

1093
01:52:34,040 --> 01:52:37,112
...there wasn't an animal
in the desert he didn't know.

1094
01:52:38,480 --> 01:52:41,233
There wasn't a star
in the firmament he hadn't named.

1095
01:52:42,440 --> 01:52:45,113
There wasn't a man he was afraid of.

1096
01:52:51,200 --> 01:52:55,910
Now the sand he fought and loved
so long has covered him at last.

1097
01:52:56,080 --> 01:52:59,356
Now he has gone into
the whole torrent of the years...

1098
01:52:59,520 --> 01:53:02,796
...of the souls that pass
and never stop.

1099
01:53:04,920 --> 01:53:07,639
In some ways he was
your dim reflection, Lord...

1100
01:53:07,800 --> 01:53:12,078
...and right or wrong,
I feel he is worth consideration.

1101
01:53:12,240 --> 01:53:14,151
But if you feel he is not...

1102
01:53:14,320 --> 01:53:18,836
...you should know that Hogue
lived then died here in the desert.

1103
01:53:19,680 --> 01:53:23,195
And I'm sure hell will
never be too hot for him.

1104
01:53:27,160 --> 01:53:29,549
He never went to church.

1105
01:53:31,200 --> 01:53:32,952
He didn't need to.

1106
01:53:33,600 --> 01:53:36,592
The whole desert was his cathedral.

1107
01:53:36,760 --> 01:53:38,193
Hold up!

1108
01:53:38,360 --> 01:53:40,794
I'm coming in tonight.

1109
01:53:41,160 --> 01:53:43,151
Hogue loved the desert...

1110
01:53:43,320 --> 01:53:45,675
...Ioved it deeper than he'd ever say.

1111
01:53:45,840 --> 01:53:48,274
He built his empire...

1112
01:53:48,440 --> 01:53:52,752
...but was man enough to give it up
for love when the time came.

1113
01:54:05,560 --> 01:54:09,712
Lord, as the day draws toward evening,
this life grows to an end for us all.

1114
01:54:09,880 --> 01:54:12,713
We say adieu to our friend.

1115
01:54:15,640 --> 01:54:17,119
Take him, Lord.

1116
01:54:22,160 --> 01:54:25,675
But knowing Cable,
I suggest you do not take him lightly.

1117
01:54:28,120 --> 01:54:29,758
Amen.

1118
